document.title: Oregon’s Transformative  Social and Emotional Learning Framework & Standards

6567EEBBCF694708B2DFB36C9805E840.description:
Reflect and evaluate the
impact of choices and
contributions in
promoting personal,
family, and community
well-being.

424077A8AB6C412FA79733371D031A61.description:
Anticipate and explain
how choices and
contributions promote
personal, family, and
community well-being.

A7BB6A1896F24FC1BAC6B0735D06FF06.description:
Make observations and
show how choices and
contributions promote
personal, family, and
community well-being.

67723B4DEFD341C08535969B7F0D43A9.description:
Identify, define and
recognize choices and
contributions in
promoting personal,
family, and community
well-being.

3F078618CCFB4F288FAB29AFFEE0BE10.description:
Anticipate, reflect and evaluate the impacts of one’s choices and contributions in
promoting personal, family, and community well-being.

844D2F3C7CED4B298FEFB8636C6E4249.description:
Design solutions for
personal and social
injustices based on
information, data, and/or
facts, and analyze the
impact of choices.

0ACF86C756A74A6089F09F971BE043AB.description:
Cite information, data,
and/or facts to develop
informed choices and
solutions for personal and
social problems.

D2AB0B36509A49F3AF7CA6F4E16A21D0.description:
Interpret, and make
observations about
information, data, and/or
facts to construct choices
and solutions for personal
and social injustices.

9B1E7227C5D343D39147351719210A82.description:
Use information, data,
and/or facts to define,
and recognize choices and
solutions for personal and
social injustices.

22DB58E274354A278C1595E36469C1C2.description:
Make informed choices and identify solutions for personal and social injustices after
analyzing all types of information.

3385D57630C34507A25162F7C2221CD2.description:
Apply the concepts of
curiosity, openmindedness, and critical
thinking to make choices
and understand the
impact across situations
and environments.

2E27A662918141D9854B17A10F3FE725.description:
Develop, explain and
investigate opportunities
to be curious, openminded, and think
critically across situations
and environments.

E5EC68EFE3EE4F4ABD031851E21C78D9.description:
Show, interpret, and
make observations of
curiosity, openmindedness, and critical
thinking across situations
and environments.

BFC9C3E03F9B4A0A9E59C8689A96CF9C.description:
Define and recognize
curiosity, openmindedness, and critical
thinking.

CF57BE3F38C44E7995A37B7520D350F0.description:
Demonstrate curiosity and open-mindedness while using critical thinking skills across
various situations and environments.

F77CA27245A74E5681821FA4B61F3FB0.description:
Demonstrate curiosity and analysis of oneself and society in order to make caring choices
that impact personal, social, and collective well-being across situations and environments.

D3D38E696EC04057B5EE0D539B1B58F0.description:
Analyze the impact of
working together to
strengthen relationships
by affirming cultural and
social perspectives.

861956C1A35646CC87B81E6D3C08A668.description:
Understand the context
and perspective from
which others are making
decisions and actively use
collaborative approaches
to problem solving.

752F921D96384FDD93DA8B4A14BE9277.description:
Use collaborative problem
solving skills to resolve
conflict in a way that is
culturally responsive to
those involved.

1DA8AAB5766A4F94B86D92355D4BAEC2.description:
Identify ways to solve a
problem that is culturally
sensitive to the
perspective of those
involved.

144BF7E973AA4891BD334094FE2BDBD7.description:
Restore relationships through actively engaging with others, working collaboratively, and
affirming cultural and social perspectives.

FB4C401B89D14F5EA70C78C25755D83F.description:
Reflect on participation in
practices that repair and
restore harm to
individuals or community
groups.

EF48D9954BB04715BC6FE087066345F0.description:
Repair and restore
relationships with
individuals and to
communities where harm
has occurred.

CDEEB4D8E08B4CF29A90236803B5BE31.description:
Recognize when a conflict
is able to be resolved
between peers and when
to seek outside support.

8ADF6381F2CE47DD8DF2888B089FA5E0.description:
Identify when someone is
experiencing harm or
when there is a conflict
that needs to be resolved.

09C0B53C13524DD9BD324D2132C7445B.description:
Recognize and acknowledge when there is harm to self and others and identify when
support, agency, and practices to repair and restore are needed.

18176EC5EDB14D94B642FC74B7ECE4A8.description:
Connect how one’s
communication and
cultural identity influence
perspectives and how it
might differ from others.

5C5110C7589C438D9517688E3E2C367E.description:
Adapt strategies for
accepting, respecting, and
supporting similarities and
differences between
oneself and others.

1DA84949147D4217BA3A1F54C729E03A.description:
Recognize how to respond
to the various social,
verbal, physical, and
situational cues of others
while practicing personal
and collective agency.

12C41C072B4C4557B36A548E75931560.description:
Understand the needs and
emotions of others, and
identify ways others are
similar and different from
oneself.

86D7DC6986924C8FAB7EFB6714F74FE7.description:
Demonstrate empathy and affirm other’s perspectives during teamwork and
collaborative problem solving.

85E176A549A44111BA6F73E4F9C8E6A1.description:
Demonstrate empathy
through various forms of
communication to work
collaboratively with
others.

7F2F2553A3BA4050BA53B7931B4FFFC0.description:
Assess communication
skills to highlight the
personal strengths and
unique contributions of
relationships with others.

CF2326054D38480FB2A184C606F47926.description:
Use strategies for
accepting, respecting, and
supporting similarities
and differences between
oneself and others.

CDFA60AFA72E43BEB904AE2A449DBC50.description:
Identify how backgrounds
can be similar and
different and recognize
that people may
experience situations
differently.

8C0F46E218554644973CC0E656F5C538.description:
Form authentic relationships that encourage autonomy while building cultural awareness
and empathy through various forms of communication.

BACB1DCD2CF14861BC23BA859B385171.description:
Establish and maintain healthy, supportive relationships and effectively navigate diverse
settings in order to collaboratively solve problems.

C16CD04B921645B3B4B665A5DB3FFA10.description:
Evaluate how one’s
responses to situations
and environments can
impact systemic injustices
and foster a sense of
belonging.

0C826C3716414FEE917517EAB8F54A62.description:
Demonstrate qualities
that foster a sense of
belonging in a diverse
community.

773B88FBFC814ABABED061FCEE5B3477.description:
Distinguish how systemic
injustices across
situations and
environments affect a
sense of belonging.

A90D561B42AD463B83BA3CFD5E9B0FC2.description:
Identify and define the
qualities of belonging
within a diverse
community.

650EA9096201471AB28463EC1070B0C2.description:
Foster a sense of belonging that cultivates acceptance, support, inclusion, and
encouragement of others within a diverse community, while addressing the impact of systemic
injustices across situations and environments.

477F257FCED84534A86ED9FACF98E1A9.description:
Analyze and critique the
health of relationships
and whether they affirm
identities and
perspectives.

2B4041A1F00845B091288292F37EE563.description:
Use social skills to
collectively achieve
mutual goals that affirm
identities and
perspectives.

DB4DE540365D4FECB11DD35E947AF6E9.description:
Recognize in oneself and
others how social skills
affect relationships and
achieving goals.

EA1DFE767359477B8C6E00DA35BDF8B6.description:
Identify the social skills
necessary for healthy
relationships and
achieving goals.

6392B137D0934E958133E246D14D768F.description:
Apply social skills (i.e., empathy, compassion, etc.) to develop and maintain healthy
relationships that collectively achieve mutual goals while affirming identities and perspectives.

9EDEF53EA98443C7B84E7315AD773A54.description:
Analyze and critique why
factors influence personal
and collective identities.

74097A755B014B73AB989F2F4A4D1ED6.description:
Formulate and assess
strategies used to affirm
personal and collective
identities.

44A53FFCD6A34ADF98C4C0A98E7D98DD.description:
Distinguish between
similarities and
differences that define
and influence personal
and collective identities.

BBD8C50DB90A4568BD8227D161BE0142.description:
Recognize and identify
factors that define and
influence personal and
collective identities.

50A1F3285B3546338DD72106996EFC13.description:
Demonstrate awareness and understanding of the similarities and differences that
define, influence, and affirm personal and collective identities.

4D45DA41FDE54918877EB182F91ACED1.description:
Develop social awareness that fosters a sense of belonging and leads to co-constructing
equitable, thriving communities and a vibrant society.

C739E389346F4703B7855D6DE566FC7D.description:
Critique and remove
barriers that restrict
personal and collective
agency.

8D80C6EA529D4419ACD1D8CD32529F4B.description:
Assess the impact of
personal and collective
agency while identifying
barriers that contribute to
or restrict agency.

699F5A7E8DAE40548F415250F5488D21.description:
Apply personal and
collective agency by
showing courage and
taking initiative.

D05075862997455189ABC91E6522CC1C.description:
Define personal and
collective agency, and
name the skills needed in
order to take initiative.

99195CAC00CF4922AE81B93AC8B6A891.description:
Develop personal and collective agency by using various forms of communication (i.e.
verbal, body language, written, etc.) to make choices and take initiative.

20AF4BF92D5D4CF9AAC86D58ADB40BED.description:
Analyze the impact of
achieving personal and
collective goals and
aspirations and make
adjustments as necessary.

8C6DDCDCF5404ECC915F6EE456867E77.description:
Assess and evaluate one’s
actions to achieve
personal and collective
goals and aspirations.

98DDD0086750460B8C623A8D52617511.description:
Construct a plan to meet
personal and collective
goals and aspirations.

C918EEB6E2BF4BFBA1BF664DCA3A59B7.description:
Identify personal and
collective goals and
aspirations.

DA56365601A446409D8E5D3691BCD579.description: Plan, evaluate, and achieve personal and collective goals and aspirations.

106B81B3E5164824B568C277A0256C1C.description:
Analyze how
management strategies
and skills impact oneself,
others, and the
community.

C496BBE4F73241DAA522CC0B69D26011.description:
Assess how the
management strategies
were used across
situations and
environments.

4DA6CCD8B5324A5B8FCBCCEF8070450A.description:
Identify which
management strategy to
use across situations and
environments.

E83C9F58C80543338C26F9E24545833C.description:
Name a variety of
management strategies
and skills.

20280DCF218246528687B9D2A6BA76C3.description:
Use management strategies while recognizing that various situations and environments
may require different approaches for achieving personal and collective goals and aspirations in ways
that affirm one’s identity.

CC5F51AD908C4819A3A20E2C041DBCBC.description:
Analyze thoughts,
emotions, impulses, and
stressors, how they are
internalized and
externalized, and the
impact these have on
oneself and others.

D3F0B8E24DFC462194C4A722B2D3BA93.description:
Compare and utilize
different strategies and
skills to manage and
express thoughts,
emotions, impulses, and
stressors.

6CC0B41A781C425A891D72B84459F82F.description:
Recognize the cause and
effect relationship of
expressing thoughts,
emotions, impulses, and
stressors across situations
and environments.

FE60C69D6BFC4CE3B0D143AFA1083251.description:
Notice and label thoughts,
emotions, impulses, and
stressors.

BF06546127364D33A486C88F4A43CB64.description:
Manage and express thoughts, emotions, impulses, and stressors in ways that affirm
one’s identity.

E3E2089A3C314A16AFFD059F66FC1B97.description:
Use management strategies to build personal and collective agency that lead to achieving
goals and aspirations.

D01A7815327E4CA38803C9F18E27F06A.description:
Analyze how one’s
intersectional identity
impacts the perspectives of
self and others, and how
this is connected to one’s
sense of belonging.

5D9169BB33954753BD319BA17B298882.description:
Assess one’s personal
assets related to
intersectional identity and
how they relate to a sense
of purpose.

A56C765418A74E2387E566F56F6F39BD.description:
Describe one’s personal and
social intersectional
identity and positionality.

EA858BFDDE804B24B7C9A78BCE48C9B6.description:
Define and ask questions
about one’s personal and
social intersectional
identity and positionality.

1EA1DD0DA5F349D9BB79F264E2FB7288.description:
Analyze personal and social intersectional identities and positionality, and how they
relate to one's interests, purpose, and sense of belonging.

6FDA3FEB9C16412CBF399AC3D7C2B8DD.description:
Analyze patterns of
behavior based on one’s
emotions, thoughts, and
perspectives over time.

83105C6F2C7E4CADA1DB473C3D0BF3AC.description:
Assess consequences of
behaviors based on one’s
emotions, thoughts, and
perspectives.

D9141C9D041D4CE4A4423C2DC34D7A84.description:
Infer causes of one’s
emotions, thoughts,
perspectives, and
behaviors.

EFC3F7BE01CB4B32966D4BFBDEF18C95.description:
Identify one’s emotions,
thoughts, perspectives,
and behaviors.

3E5156BD440C4DF484B79456D9CC6FC3.description:
Reflect on and evaluate how one’s emotions, thoughts, and perspectives (including
values, biases, and prejudices) can influence behavior.

434B00728DC24CB3BCD1759FA9DD303E.description:
Apply concepts of the
stress response system to
identify tools to help
regulate across situations
and environments.

AE83C608DE184DF480CDB000368A5D59.description:
Draw conclusions about
what stress response
state that one is
experiencing based on the
identified cues.

473299699526407291FF3D85784AC7CD.description:
Interpret environmental
and experiential cues for
dysregulation that
activate the stress
response system, and
what environments or
experiences support
regulation.

0646D5BF8A6642D8998336D7FB7ED034.description:
Identify physiological cues
related to the stress
response system and
what they look like, feel
like, and sound like.

9950A23AD90F4C02ABAD6C14DD63CA19.description:
Understand the stress response system (regulation and dysregulation) and what
environments and experiences activate those responses.

FC1DC47B682B4C93A48FB540F2723DC9.description:
Connect emotions,
thoughts, strengths, and
potential to developing
interests and sense of
purpose.

5B32FD66B9A14B1288ECCB3CB7F21524.description:
Investigate areas of
strength, growth, interest
and passion that signal
strong emotions and
responses.

BA65979FEC5E432A9E4C52737F37F203.description:
Describe the intensity of
emotions, thoughts,
strengths and potential,
and how they can
fluctuate and change.

D2C960EE46FB44FEB566F6C824393463.description:
Name emotions,
thoughts, strengths and
potential.

4736699E805B44CCB7DDB0972F6EB53B.description:
Identify and label emotions, thoughts, strengths, and potential (both personal and
cultural).

30C9BB356864433D8AF52F1D7EC06FA7.description:
Identify and reflect upon one’s thoughts, emotions, behaviors, intersectional identity, and
capabilities across situations and environments.
